# Prototypes Monorepo - Cursor AI Rules

## Project Context
This is a monorepo for Angular prototypes using Supernova design system.

## Key Directories
- `apps/` - Angular prototypes (standalone components)
- `apps/gallery/` - Gallery website on port 3000
- `apps/prototype-template/` - Template for new prototypes
- `packages/supernova-sdk/` - Shared design tokens & assets
- `packages/theme-toggle/` - Reusable theme toggle component

## Common Scripts
When users say "start the gallery", run: `./start-gallery.sh`
When users say "start all prototypes", run: `./start-all.sh`
When users say "create a new prototype", run: `./create-prototype.sh`
When users say "stop everything", run: `./stop-all.sh`

**Important:** Always prefer .sh scripts over npm commands. Scripts handle permissions better and auto-manage ports.
If scripts fail, npm commands can be used as fallback (e.g., `npm run dev -w @prototypes/name`).

## Tech Stack
- Angular 21 with standalone components
- TypeScript 5.9.2
- SCSS for styling
- Vitest for testing
- Supernova design tokens

## Design System Standards
- ALWAYS use Supernova design tokens (no hardcoded colors/spacing)
- Import tokens: `@import '@prototypes/supernova-sdk/output/tokens/tokens';`
- Never hardcode colors/spacing when DS tokens exist
- Match Figma designs pixel-perfect. Do not guess. Use as a reference.
- When a Figma link is given, use Figma MCP to fecth all the specs (tokens, colors, measurements, typography, etc)

## Component Standards
- Always use standalone: `standalone: true`
- Always include provideAnimations() in app.config.ts
- Component files: component-name.ts, .html, .scss
- Use Angular animations from '@angular/animations'

## Documentation
All documentation is in the docs/ folder:
- docs/SCRIPTS.md - All available scripts explained
- docs/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md - Best practices and patterns
- docs/QUICK_REFERENCE.md - Quick command reference
- docs/START_HERE.md - Getting started guide

## Package Naming
- Format: `@prototypes/prototype-name`
- Use kebab-case for names

## When Creating Components
- Include animations when appropriate
- Use design tokens for all colors/spacing
- Follow BEM naming in SCSS
- Import from '@prototypes/supernova-sdk'

## Common Tasks
- Start development: `./start-prototype.sh [name]` (recommended) or `npm run dev -w @prototypes/[name]` (fallback)
- Create prototype: `./create-prototype.sh`
- Update gallery: `./sync-gallery.sh`
- Check setup: `./check-prerequisites.sh`
- Start gallery: `./start-gallery.sh`
- Start all: `./start-all.sh`
- Stop all: `./stop-all.sh`

## Angular Patterns (All Prototypes)
- Use standalone components (no NgModules)
- Always include provideAnimations() in app.config.ts
- Component structure: .ts, .html, .scss files
- Import tokens: import { DesignTokens } from '@prototypes/supernova-sdk'